<TITLE> 5 of family die in Sitakunda fire </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Feb 20 (bdnews24.com)  Five of a family died in their sleep early Friday morning when a house caught fire at Doaji Para of Sitakunda Sadar Upazila in the district. Abul Bashar, wife Selina Akter, 35, and their sons Sourav Hossain, 17, Sabuj Hossain, and Sajib Hossain, 3, died in the one-hour fire. Fire service and Upazila administration officials said fire broke out in the house, next to a candle factory, around 1:30am. The flames spread fast, giving the family no chance to escape. Bashar used to supply candles to Sitakunda and other areas. Fire service officer Fazlul Quader told bdnews24.com the electric short-circuit sparked the flames. He said the victims died from burns and suffocation before they had reached the scene of the accident. They doused the flames around 2:45am and retrieved the charred bodies. He added assets worth Tk 3 lakh were lost to the fire. Upazila Nirbahi Officer Abdur Rauf told bdnews24.com they would give "the family of the deceased" Tk 50000.
